<title>USA: IBM to pay Sears $450 million for rest of Advantis.</title>
<headline>IBM to pay Sears $450 million for rest of Advantis.</headline>
<dateline>SOMERS, N.Y. 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>International Business Machines Corp. said Thursday it agreed to buy the rest of its 70-percent owned Advantis computer services company from 30-percent owner Sears, Roebuck &amp; Co. for $450 million.</p>
<p>IBM, the world's largest computer maker, said it would fold Advantis more fully into its Global Services arm, the fastest growing part of its business. Sears, the nation's second-largest retailer, said the sale would help it focus on its core business and that it expected a pretax gain of about $150 million on the sale.</p>
</text>
